      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@maba, he&#39;s talking about isA for some reason, which captures the class, it accepts <code>Class&lt;T&gt;</code> instead of <code>Class&lt;?&gt;</code> (which is what instanceOf does). Since it captures the class, it would be a compile time error to do isA with a class incompatible to the instance. <a href=\"https://github.com/hamcrest/JavaHamcrest/issues/39\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">github.com/hamcrest/JavaHamcrest/issues/39</a>"
